<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-C363DEF6-7E13-4C80-853C-77BAC2CB529E" version="4" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-C363DEF6-7E13-4C80-853C-77BAC2CB529E" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">05 How to adjust the strip support (to avoid bouncing)</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-173AF84C-D126-4DD5-8ABA-ADD08113B9D4"><p class="- topic/p ">This document describes the adjustment of the strip support to avoid, for example, bouncing of the support strip against the top cover. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The strip support is mounted between the guidance and the printhead carriage. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Make this adjustment after you replace an ink tube, air tube, fiber cable, flex cable or the metal strip. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Next do the same adjustment in case a bouncing (noise) of the strip support against the top cover is noticeable. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Adjustment</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-982BAB96-F1AC-436A-A6A8-B6CC211033FE" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><p class="- topic/p "> A training video is available in the training video section: See 
<xref href="http://localhost:20346/VIDEO00394EN.US/video11/index.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>How to adjust the strip support to avoid bouncing</xref> 
</p><ul id="UL_FC1647DBE66F40EAAF0086BB3E0A9CE1" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_E562AA275D63474CB2E1FE6DD165A477" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the top cover. 
</p></li></ul></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_A392D23B9FA5434A8095E72A33F001E1" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_BFC835835B5440A98A2DF72417BDB02D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20 
</p></li><li id="LI_50BCE33E1BE540B7B863D5726E371F62" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Caliper. 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">3 cable ties 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-CA588BE7-B261-4C41-8EAF-46787DC93926" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">To do</title><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Switch the printer on 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-DB340B14-87E5-4FDB-8108-245D16C84FF1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-C91A15EB-D315-43C8-A8E0-AE6ED77DD763" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-6F82EA64-D21F-44D9-A5C4-42A0977D887F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6F82EA64-D21F-44D9-A5C4-42A0977D887F-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The video "How to adjust strip support" explains the procedure. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="http://localhost:20346/VIDEO00394EN.US/video11/index.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>How to adjust strip support</xref> 
</p></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to adjust the strip support</title><table id="GUID-BDB87D50-9E70-4086-AC9E-FA7970C76B0D" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the right side top cover to get access to the cable ties. 
<xref href="GUID-F53C0184-B1EA-4AA3-A93E-FA5DB552BE10.xml" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>24 How to remove the right side top cover</xref>
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-5CCF2366-01C4-4E9E-A2A2-5EE5378C48A3" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-6F59E04D-D916-4EFD-A205-580D7E547C30-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6F59E04D-D916-4EFD-A205-580D7E547C30-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Cut the 3 cable ties. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-28A44E86-4246-45DA-9B33-D36EBF9D13BE" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-BF515D8E-D86C-4C08-8956-624BA6DBF3C1-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BF515D8E-D86C-4C08-8956-624BA6DBF3C1-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Loosen the 8 screws as shown. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-7F80B3B0-22C9-4561-813C-532818BCF2EC" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-FEB798A9-85C7-4A69-9EFB-6925F5CFDF4F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FEB798A9-85C7-4A69-9EFB-6925F5CFDF4F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Create some space in the ink tubing package. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-222F589D-CB19-416B-AAF0-A593E6582E00" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-8342D58F-FAAD-4AE8-96B4-24A54DF4ED40-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8342D58F-FAAD-4AE8-96B4-24A54DF4ED40-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-3BF883A3-B83B-46C4-B3BB-2F63A76AAADA" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-071C2909-1C47-4288-BB62-5325AD2965B3-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-071C2909-1C47-4288-BB62-5325AD2965B3-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the carriage on the left-hand side. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-3885263C-D615-4528-8DFD-B0016CA172BF" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-DCF51D50-B854-4ABF-9ADA-97882D4666F5-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DCF51D50-B854-4ABF-9ADA-97882D4666F5-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Move each 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">black</b> bracket to the 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">right-hand</b> side till it is blocked. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-DCA0F12F-433C-436B-BC54-490B1BF41DDA" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-6D0E368F-3276-4EF4-A48D-DDF6BC497940-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6D0E368F-3276-4EF4-A48D-DDF6BC497940-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Move each 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">white</b> bracket to the<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> right-hand</b> side, 45mm from the black bracket 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-6F000187-D435-43AF-A9CA-79BDCC7C7D2C" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-EAB20862-AAFA-4951-94DE-283C70DA1828-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EAB20862-AAFA-4951-94DE-283C70DA1828-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Fill up the space in the metal plate curve by pushing down (1), pulling back (2) and lifting up (3) the tubing package. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-338A8D65-D437-45EF-A337-44EBB4D3C78A" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-6F82EA64-D21F-44D9-A5C4-42A0977D887F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6F82EA64-D21F-44D9-A5C4-42A0977D887F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Center the metal support strip. If needed make an adjustment. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Find below the link to the video "How to adjust the strip support to avoid bouncing". 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="http://localhost:20346/VIDEO00394EN.US/video11/index.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>How to adjust the strip support to avoid bouncing</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-B046D00B-F277-40FB-A22A-4228C9170C97" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-1ADFCB26-F692-4021-A5ED-0F4F362B507D-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1ADFCB26-F692-4021-A5ED-0F4F362B507D-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Manually move the carriage from left to right. 3 times in each direction. The tubes can settle on the strip support assembly. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-E8B8BCE3-3590-439F-AE91-01ECAB8A94FB" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-31295402-4FA0-4A0A-8525-BF9938BE7AA8-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-31295402-4FA0-4A0A-8525-BF9938BE7AA8-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">To fixate the tubes position in the strip support tighten the 8 screws as shown. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-0B0C3303-8F22-4618-B457-CEEB1CD03706" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-7AF4F729-EA19-45F6-8784-2FE1EBA142D7-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7AF4F729-EA19-45F6-8784-2FE1EBA142D7-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Close the top cover and start sds test 56004, Measure uniformity of carriage speed. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-D6ED8AB0-936C-48BB-9515-0DB00ECA6111" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-6858E03C-213C-4F2F-B894-18E9E2C2A92F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6858E03C-213C-4F2F-B894-18E9E2C2A92F-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-F4FF98AF-3DA0-4890-B36C-56F694D43FA1" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-4D153748-79EE-495C-9FF8-053DC3C0028C-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4D153748-79EE-495C-9FF8-053DC3C0028C-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">13 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Ensure the strip support is not bouncing and doesn't touch the top cover. 
</p><note id="GUID-026BB13E-B7F1-4A0C-B0C7-DC61AF15E0DA" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "><?xm-replace_text Paragraph?>
</p></note><p class="- topic/p ">In case the this is not correct 2 solutions are advised. 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Reverse the current installed metal strip. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Install a new strip 
</p></li></ol><p class="- topic/p ">The document and video "How to exchange the metal strip of the strip support" explains these procedures. 
<xref href="GUID-53D4F91E-5AFE-4299-AE69-C14CC7C9FDA3.xml" scope="local" format="dita" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>05 How to remove the strip support (metal strip)</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">14 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Finally place the 3 new cable ties and place the remaining covers. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-2C68E427-8B28-40FD-BEAD-FDDADE6CA760" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-BF515D8E-D86C-4C08-8956-624BA6DBF3C1-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BF515D8E-D86C-4C08-8956-624BA6DBF3C1-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-6674B267-4A91-406A-80DB-0D97B7385C72" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-D51EA3F5-D1B4-4083-AF8D-D65E24550205-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D51EA3F5-D1B4-4083-AF8D-D65E24550205-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-BB9FFD1B-E53B-488A-980C-657E28D40896.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Adjustment</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>